        "content": "<p>Consider the following data structure:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">debug_flags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">option_a</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">16</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">option_b</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">16</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bitfields</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>When generating the rust bindings, I get an error: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0588</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">packed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">cannot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">transitively</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">contain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"cp\">#[repr(align)]</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>What is the recommended way to work around this issue ?</p>",
        "id": 510993608,
        "sender_full_name": "Jayaura",
        "timestamp": 1744134606
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was able to get around the issue by marking the type opaque.</p>",
        "id": 511023607,
        "sender_full_name": "Jayaura",
        "timestamp": 1744145533
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"613686\">Jayaura</span> has marked this topic as resolved.</p>",
        "id": 511023618,
        "sender_full_name": "Notification Bot",
        "timestamp": 1744145538
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"613686\">Jayaura</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/.E2.9C.94.20Rust.20binding.20for.20struct.20fields.20with.20bit.20width/near/511023607\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I was able to get around the issue by marking the type opaque.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yeah, if you don't need to peek into it, that is what we do. If you do need, then you can e.g. access it via C.</p>\n<p>We are hoping for upstream Rust + <code>bindgen</code> for those -- please see <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/issues/353\">https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/issues/353</a>.</p>",
        "id": 511027437,
